sup> <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Combinatorial_number_theory" =
class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Combinatorial number theory">combinatorial n=
umber theory</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_ref-17" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory#cite_note-17"><span class=3D"cite-=
bracket">[</span>16<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Computational_number_theory" title=3D"Com=
putational number theory">computational number theory</a>,<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_=
theory#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>17<span class=3D"=
cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and applied number theory, which examines =
the application of number theory to science and technology.<sup id=3D"cite_=
ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number=
_theory#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=3D=
