<p>In recorded history, knowledge of numbers existed in the ancient civilis=
ations of Mesopotamia, Egypt, China, and India.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" clas=
s=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory#cite=
_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>19<span class=3D"cite-bracke=
t">]</span></a></sup> The earliest historical find of an arithmetical natur=
e is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plimpton_322" title=3D"Pl=
impton 322">Plimpton 322</a>, dated c.&nbsp;1800&nbsp;BC. It is a broken cl=
