<p>Elementary number theory deals with the topics in number theory by means=
 of basic methods in arithmetic.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:1_4-1" class=3D"refere=
nce"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory#cite_note-:1-4"=
><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>4<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span=
></a></sup> Its primary subjects of study are <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Divisibility" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Divisibility">divi=
sibility</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Factorization" title=
=3D"Factorization">factorization</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.o=
rg/wiki/Primality" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Primality">primality</a>,=
 as well as <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modular_arithmetic" ti=
tle=3D"Modular arithmetic">congruences</a> in <a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Modular_arithmetic" title=3D"Modular arithmetic">modular arithm=
etic</a>.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-75" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.=
wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory#cite_note-75"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>71<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup><sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-:3_13-1" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nu=
mber_theory#cite_note-:3-13"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>12<span c=
lass=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Other topics in elementary number =
theory include <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diophantine_equatio=
n" title=3D"Diophantine equation">Diophantine equations</a>, <a href=3D"htt=
ps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Continued_fractions" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=
=3D"Continued fractions">continued fractions</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Integer_partition" title=3D"Integer partition">integer part=
itions</a>, and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diophantine_approx=
imation" title=3D"Diophantine approximation">Diophantine approximations</a>=
.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-:2_76-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wik=
ipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory#cite_note-:2-76"><span class=3D"cite-bracket"=
>[</span>72<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p><p>Arithmetic is the study of numerical operations and investigates how=
 numbers are combined and transformed using the arithmetic operations of <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Addition" title=3D"Addition">additio=
n</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subtraction" title=3D"Subtr=
action">subtraction</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Multiplic=
ation" title=3D"Multiplication">multiplication</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Division_(mathematics)" title=3D"Division (mathematics)">=
division</a>, <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Exponentiation" titl=
e=3D"Exponentiation">exponentiation</a>, extraction of <a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nth_root" title=3D"Nth root">roots</a>, and <a href=3D=
"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Logarithm" title=3D"Logarithm">logarithms</a=
>. Multiplication, for instance, is an operation that combines two numbers,=
