 is the largest of such divisors. Two integers are said to be coprime or re=
latively prime to one another if their greatest common divisor, and simulta=
neously their only divisor, is 1. The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w=
iki/Euclidean_algorithm" title=3D"Euclidean algorithm">Euclidean algorithm<=
/a> computes the greatest common divisor of two integers <span class=3D"mwe=
