<p>Analytic number theory, in contrast to elementary number theory, relies =
on <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_numbers" class=3D"mw-re=
direct" title=3D"Complex numbers">complex numbers</a> and techniques from a=
nalysis and calculus. Analytic number theory may be defined
</p>
<ul><li>in terms of its tools, as the study of the integers by means of too=
ls from <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_analysis" title=3D"Re=
al analysis">real</a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_=
analysis" title=3D"Complex analysis">complex</a> analysis;<sup id=3D"cite_r=
